features.text: After arriving in complete darkness at the remote little hamlet of Shingle Street, UK, in the midst of a large storm, it seemed that the journey would be wasted. Then miraculously, just as the sun rose above the horizon, the clouds parted, illuminating the coastguard's cottages in intense light against the brooding sky for a few magical minutes.

A personal favourite from my Dark Thoughts series: a collection of landscapes, seascapes and cityscapes with a dystopian twist. The inspiration for these images was born from a 1970's and 80's childhood of unsettling children's television, MR James ghost stories, frankly horrific public information films, and of course the ever present shadow of total nuclear annihilation.

 
 

 
 .
 
 
From the Dark Thoughts series. Regeneration of the Docklands area of London. Always keep building.
